[The state of Pennsylvania can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3332545,8442. Erie County, with a population of 280 566 in 2010, is located in the northwest corner of US state of Pennsylvania on the shore of Lake Erie (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erie_County,_Pennsylvania). For a map of Pennsylvania, showing the location of Erie County, see http://geology.com/county-map/pennsylania-county-map.gif.

Please see the moderator's comments in prior ProMED-mail posts on syphilis for discussions of this disease. The news report above says that there is a rise in the incidence of syphilis in Erie County, but does not indicate any characteristics of those with syphilis.

A detailed description of the cases in Erie County is essential so that efforts to limit potential spread of syphilis can be effectively targeted. More information in this regard from knowledgeable sources would be appreciated. - Mod.ML]
